{
  "texts": [
    "Instead of staking currency as in PoS, users must prove their real identities.",
    "The purpose of PoA is to create an authorized block validator user for the person who created the block, and it is a more centralized consensus mechanism compared to PoS.",
    "A limited number of users are trusted, pre-approved, and allowed by the network, and they are identified by a unique ID known as authorities [42].",
    "All blocks are created by selected authorized users, which reduces the time required to generate blocks and resolve data consistency issues [43].",
    "FragmentationData Fragmentation is the splitting of large data into an optimum number of fragments."
  ]
}